# Terminal Setup

## Local environment

- Shell: fish (built-in autosuggestions + tab completion — no plugins needed)
- History: Atuin (`~/.atuin/bin/atuin`) — visual ctrl-r search
- Prompt: Starship (`/opt/homebrew/bin/starship`)
- Terminal: Ghostty + Catppuccin Mocha

---

## SSH to remote hosts — lazy bootstrap

Use `sshr <host>` instead of `ssh <host>`. On first connect it installs fish,
starship, and atuin on the remote (user-level, no root required unless installing
fish via apt). On every connect it syncs the config files so changes made locally
propagate automatically.

### Tools installed on remote hosts

| Tool | Location on remote | How |
|---|---|---|
| fish | system (e.g. `/usr/bin/fish`) | `apt/dnf/yum install fish` (needs sudo) |
| starship | `~/.local/bin/starship` | binary uploaded from local |
| atuin | `~/.local/bin/atuin` | binary uploaded from local |

### Local files created by this setup

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `~/.ssh/cm/` | ControlMaster socket directory |
| `~/.ssh/bootstrapped_hosts` | Log of every host bootstrapped |
| `~/.local/lib/starship-linux/starship-x86_64` | Linux starship binary (x86_64) |
| `~/.local/lib/starship-linux/starship-aarch64` | Linux starship binary (aarch64) |
| `~/.local/lib/atuin-linux/atuin-x86_64` | Linux atuin binary (x86_64) |
| `~/.local/lib/atuin-linux/atuin-aarch64` | Linux atuin binary (aarch64) |
| `~/.config/starship.toml` | Starship config — synced to remotes on every connect |
| `~/.config/fish/remote_config.fish` | Fish config synced to `~/.config/fish/config.fish` on remotes |
| `~/.config/fish/functions/sshr.fish` | `sshr` wrapper function |

### Changes to existing files

**`~/.ssh/config`** — added to the `Host *` block:
```
ControlMaster auto
ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm/%r@%h:%p
ControlPersist 10m
ServerAliveInterval 30
ServerAliveCountMax 3
```

### What gets written on each remote host

| Remote path | Source |
|---|---|
| `~/.local/bin/starship` | `~/.local/lib/starship-linux/starship-<arch>` |
| `~/.local/bin/atuin` | `~/.local/lib/atuin-linux/atuin-<arch>` |
| `~/.config/starship.toml` | `~/.config/starship.toml` (re-synced every connect) |
| `~/.config/fish/config.fish` | `~/.config/fish/remote_config.fish` (re-synced every connect) |

### Usage

```fish
sshr fastpi          # first connect: bootstraps everything
sshr fastpi          # subsequent: syncs configs and connects instantly
```

### Atuin history on remote

Each host starts with an empty history database. History builds up as you use
the shell. To share history across all machines, run on remote after first connect:

```fish
atuin login   # then: atuin sync
```

---

## Reverting everything

### Remove from a single remote host

```bash
ssh <host> 'rm -f ~/.local/bin/starship ~/.local/bin/atuin ~/.config/starship.toml ~/.config/fish/config.fish'
# fish was installed via apt — to remove it too:
ssh <host> 'sudo apt-get remove -y fish'
```

### Remove from all remote hosts (Ansible)

```bash
ansible all -i hosts.ini -m shell -a \
  'rm -f ~/.local/bin/starship ~/.local/bin/atuin ~/.config/starship.toml ~/.config/fish/config.fish'
```

### Remove local files

```bash
# Binaries
rm -rf ~/.local/lib/starship-linux/
rm -rf ~/.local/lib/atuin-linux/
rmdir ~/.local/lib 2>/dev/null   # only removes it if now empty; safe to ignore error

# sshr function and remote config templates
rm ~/.config/fish/functions/sshr.fish
rm ~/.config/fish/remote_config.fish

# Starship config (only if you didn't have one before this setup)
rm ~/.config/starship.toml

# Host log
rm ~/.ssh/bootstrapped_hosts

# ControlMaster sockets — list, kill, then remove directory
ls ~/.ssh/cm/
ssh -O exit git@github.com   # repeat for each socket listed
rm -f ~/.ssh/cm/*
rmdir ~/.ssh/cm
```

### Revert ~/.ssh/config

Remove these five lines from the `Host *` block:

```
ControlMaster auto
ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm/%r@%h:%p
ControlPersist 10m
ServerAliveInterval 30
ServerAliveCountMax 3
```
